To install esphome, do this:

git clone https://github.com/esphome/esphome.git
cd esphome
git checkout dev
./script/setup

To use esphome from the command line, activate the python
virtual environment in your terminal shell like this:

source venv/bin/activate

and the you can cd into the growOS/esphome directory and setup
your secrets file by doing this:

cp secrets.$USER secrets.yaml

Now you are ready to build and run!

esphome compile cpu0.yaml
esphome upload cpu0.yaml
esphome logs cpu0.yaml

or do all three in one shot using this command:

esphome run cpu0.yaml

Also, you can connect to the growboard's IP address from a browser
to see the information and flip some switches.

Voila!

